dc_title_s: Dickinson County, Iowa, 1949, aerial photomosaic index
dc_description_s: Title supplied by cataloger based on information from sheet label. Image is a photoreduction of the mosaic created from original aerial photographs. Designating symbol BZL. Form of individual image numbering: BZL-1F-[number], or BZL-2F-[number]."Flying completed 7-4-49." Flown by Woltz Studios, Des Moines, Iowa. "Approximate scale, 1:20,000" [refers to individual images from which mosaic was made].|Contact the Map Collection at The University of Iowa Libraries: http://www.lib.uiowa.edu/maps/contact/
